rComments: Fantasy and Horror. Very nice, informative professor with a genuine interest in the material. I liked that she chose some obscure texts like Lord Dunsany, as well as some mainstream ones like Gaiman. She was always very helpful and clear, and never seemed to be in a bad mood. I'd take another of her classes eagerly.

Really lovely professor; very knowledgeable in her field, unusually shy of making comparisons to movies. Leads discussion well, and makes even dreaded books fun to talk about. Kind and insightful marker, has good teaching method. Easygoing and sweet-natured. Only complaint: puts out-of-print works on syllabus.
Gothic Lit.  Good class, interesting.  Heavy reading load, but well worth it.  Professor is super understanding and gives extentions no problem.

Absolutely best professor ever!  Extremely smart, friendly, understanding and funny. She's very easy to talk to. Heavy reading load, but most works are worth reading. Tests are very fair and she is willing to help whenever you need it.  Best Prof. ever!!!
